<figureCitation id="130390CB2816FF878E29B3DAFD1FFB44" box="[601,704,1155,1179]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 7" captionStart-1="FIGURE 8" captionStart-2="FIGURE 9" captionStart-3="FIGURE 10" captionStart-4="FIGURE 11" captionStartId-0="14.[151,250,1602,1626]" captionStartId-1="16.[151,250,1156,1180]" captionStartId-2="17.[151,250,1302,1326]" captionStartId-3="18.[151,250,1570,1594]" captionStartId-4="20.[151,250,1790,1814]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,453,1579]" captionTargetBox-1="[152,1436,345,1133]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1434,525,1279]" captionTargetBox-3="[151,1434,346,1547]" captionTargetBox-4="[151,1436,957,1767]" captionTargetId-0="figure-134@14.[151,1436,453,1579]" captionTargetId-1="figure-97@16.[152,1436,345,1133]" captionTargetId-2="figure-151@17.[151,1436,525,1279]" captionTargetId-3="figure-92@18.[151,1436,345,1547]" captionTargetId-4="figure-372@20.[151,1436,957,1767]" captionTargetPageId-0="14" captionTargetPageId-1="16" captionTargetPageId-2="17" captionTargetPageId-3="18" captionTargetPageId-4="20" captionText-0="FIGURE 7. Chloeia nuriae sp. n., holotype (EMU 13145). A. Dorsal view, recently collected. B. Anterior end, dorsal view. C. Prostomium and caruncle. D. Neurochaeta from first chaetiger. E. Neurochaeta from same chaetiger 10. F. Notochaetae from first chaetiger. G. Notochaeta from chaetiger 10. H. Pigmentation pattern from median segments. I. Posterior end with cirriform lobes. A, D–I. Holotype; B, C. Paratypes (ADC: accessory cirriform branchiae, Br: bipinnate branchiae, DC: dorsal cirri, Li: lips, LL: lateral lobes, MA: median antenna, ML: median lobe, Pa: palps, PA: paired antennae). Scale bars: A, 5 mm; B, C, 1 mm; D, 20 μm; E, 15 μm; F, G, 50 μm; H, 2 mm; I, 0.5 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 8. Chloeia paulayi sp. n. A. Holotype (UF 493), dorsal view, depressed by glass slide, after Methyl Green staining. B. Same, anterior region, dorsal view. C. Same, left lateral view. D. Same, ventral view. E. Paratype (UF 493b), anterior region, dorsal view. F. Same, close-up of anterior end. Scale bars: A, E 2.2 mm; B, F, 1.3 mm; C, 0.9 mm; D, 1.8 mm." captionText-2="FIGURE 9. Chloeia paulayi sp. n. A. Holotype (UF 493), chaetiger 1, notochaetal tips. B. Paratype (UF 493b), chaetiger 16, notochaetae. C. Holotype, chaetiger 4, neurochaetae. Scale bars: A: 45 µm, B: 90 µm, C: 30 µm." captionText-3="FIGURE 10. Chloeia pinnata Moore, 1911, holotype (USNM 16842).A,Anteriorend, dorsal view. B. Segment 3. C.Prostomium and caruncle. D. Segments 3 and 4. E. Pigmentation pattern from median segments. F. Neurochaeta from first chaetiger. G. Long neurochaeta from chaetiger 10. H. Short neurochaeta from same chaetiger. I. Notochaeta from first chaetiger, insert shows the serrated inner border. J. Notochaeta from chaetiger 10. C. Paratype, all other holotype; B, C. White arrows show branchiae (Li: lips, LL: lateral lobes, MA: median antenna, ML: median lobe, Pa: palps, PA: paired antennae). Scale bars: A, C, D, 1 mm; B, E, 0.5 mm; F–H, 10 μm; I, 40 μm (inset 25 μm); J, 50 μm." captionText-4="FIGURE 11. Chloeia pseudeuglochis Augener, 1922, holotype (ZMH V-7466). A. Dorsal view. B. Oblique, dorsal view. C. Anterior end, dorsal view. D. Labels. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.4 mm; C, 0.7 mm (Photos: Alexandra Kerbl)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480003" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480005" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480007" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480009" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480011" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6480003/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6480005/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6480007/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6480009/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6480011/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="516">Figs 7–11</figureCitation>
